<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,582,1147]" box="[151,937,582,607]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Black with apex of scutellum and apical area of forewing light brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,582,1147]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis box="[199,372,618,643]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer with caudal margin almost truncate, ventral margin straight with long stout setae on caudal one third. Subgenital plate with rounded caudal margin, with fine short hairlike setae. Style linear with well developed preapical lobe, apical apophysis fingerlike, slightly curved laterally, with corrugated surface. Connective with arms shorter than stem. Aedeagus with well developed dorsal apodeme, preatrium reduced; shaft directed caudodorsally, broad basally, gradually tapering towards apex, hooked with U-shaped notch; lateral margins near apical 0.33 serrated, one or two rows of spicules on apical 0.33 length; gonopore apical.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,582,1147]" box="[199,505,834,859]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis box="[199,277,834,859]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Length</emphasis>
. Male: 4.0– 
<quantity box="[412,501,835,859]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.4" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" unit="mm" value="4.4">4.4 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
